written one day.

Version info:

Version 0.6 B(eta)
This version of BreakEdit is not yet complete.

The following features are not implemented at all:

- Moving levels.
- Several drawing tools are not implemented.
    - Fill
    - Clear
    - Copy
    - Palette. This feature will probably be replaced
               by the set-editor
- Advanced memory info does not exist yet.
- There is no online help yet.
- There is no way yet to load in a different gfx set.
- There is no way to create a new gfx-set yet.

The following features are only partially implemented:

- Mouse control in editor- & sub- screens.
- Several sub-screens need to be redesigned.
- No message is given when a value is out of range.
  the value will be set to it's maximum/minimum, though.
- Deleting levels.

The Following bugs are known:

- BreakEdit may try to load corrupt packages.
- Several variables are not updated on the menu correctly when loading.
- Several functions reset input each time they are used.
- Zone numbers are shown at the top of the edit-screen
- Text may appear incomplete. This appears to be an AMOS problem.
- The name fields contains a bug, the del key does not always
  work properly.
- Occasionaly, when deleting the last level, an empty one will
  appear instead of it being deleted properly.

